Abby, do you mind if I hide down here?

175
00:06:56,710 --> 00:06:58,310
麦基快把我搞疯了...
McGee is driving me crazy with all...

176
00:07:01,014 --> 00:07:02,848
小野猫 这又是哪一出?
What's new, pussycat?

177
00:07:02,883 --> 00:07:04,016
你听见我说的了吧
I guess you heard.

178
00:07:04,050 --> 00:07:05,851
呃 关于现实生活种的超级英雄?
Um, about the Real- Life Superheroes?

179
00:07:05,886 --> 00:07:07,853
喂!我可是为了联系上
Hello! I've been trying to meet

180
00:07:07,888 --> 00:07:09,388
Cataonic花了几个月的时间啊
Catatonic for, like, months.

181
00:07:09,423 --> 00:07:10,955
他拯救动物 大部分是猫
He rescues animals, mostly cats.

182
00:07:10,989 --> 00:07:12,490
他在庇护所里就像
And he's like a rock star

183
00:07:12,525 --> 00:07:14,125
摇滚明星一样火
in the shelter community.

184
00:07:14,159 --> 00:07:16,594
现在我们法庭需要一个摇滚明星
Right now we need a rock star in the forensic community.

185
00:07:16,629 --> 00:07:18,763
我正在研究你在保险柜找到的
I am making some progress on the chewed fingernails

186
00:07:18,798 --> 00:07:20,131
那些凶手咬下来的指甲
that you found at the safe.

187
00:07:20,165 --> 00:07:21,599
可能 就是 有的...
Maybe, like, some...

188
00:07:21,634 --> 00:07:24,268
有的凶手开锁时比较紧张才会咬指甲
some nervous murderer trying to pick a lock

189
00:07:24,303 --> 00:07:26,103
我正在做DNA配对 不过...
I'm running the DNA now, but...

190
00:07:26,138 --> 00:07:29,105
我有重大发现
my big find was online.

191
00:07:29,140 --> 00:07:31,374
我发现这个徽章 看起来很眼熟
I noticed this insignia, and it looked familiar.

192
00:07:31,409 --> 00:07:34,144
然后我想起来我是从哪儿看来的了
And then I remembered where I knew it from.

193
00:07:34,178 --> 00:07:37,347
六个月前一场酒吧斗殴事件
There was a bar fight uploaded to CyberVid

194
00:07:37,381 --> 00:07:38,715
被传到在CyberVid网
six months ago.

195
00:07:38,750 --> 00:07:40,584
我可不想找麻烦 你想怎么样?
I don't want any trouble! You don't want any trouble?

196
00:07:40,618 --> 00:07:42,352
不! 真糟糕 是你找到的
No! Too bad 'cause you found it!

197
00:07:42,386 --> 00:07:44,720
你个傻子 是你找到的! 让他走吧!
No, punk, you found it! Let him go!

198
00:07:44,755 --> 00:07:46,756
嘿 老兄 放开我 你个神经病!
Hey, man, let go of me, you freak!

199
00:07:51,227 --> 00:07:53,596
瓦里斯和墨菲拦住了那个肇事者
Wallace and Murphy stopped the bad guy.

200
00:07:53,630 --> 00:07:57,633
耶! 后来这个视频火了
Yay! So, the video went viral,

201
00:07:57,668 --> 00:07:59,835
他们就变成了当地人们的英雄了
and they became local heroes.

202
00:07:59,869 --> 00:08:01,970
那个醉鬼...就那个看起来像醉鬼的
The drunk idiot... Looks like a drunk idiot.

203
00:08:02,004 --> 00:08:03,371
好像很忌恨的样子
Maybe he's holding a grudge.

204
00:08:03,405 --> 00:08:04,639
你查到他的身份了吗?
You got an I.D.?

205
00:08:04,674 --> 00:08:07,576
呃 我还无法通过面部识别查到这个人
Well, I haven't had any hits on facial recognition.

206
00:08:07,610 --> 00:08:09,377
那么到底是谁拍下的这个视频?
So, who shot this video?

207
00:08:09,411 --> 00:08:13,147
是一个名叫ICU的用户上传的
It was uploaded by a user called ICU.

208
00:08:13,182 --> 00:08:16,283
我追踪不到这个人的真实身份
Had trouble tracking that back to an actual person.

209
00:08:16,317 --> 00:08:18,686
不过不管是谁 他肯定费劲了心思
Whoever did this went to a lot of trouble

210
00:08:18,720 --> 00:08:20,488
隐藏他的身份
to keep his identity hidden.

211
00:08:20,522 --> 00:08:22,289
走着瞧
Keep looking.

212
00:08:28,830 --> 00:08:30,563
原来你在这儿
There you are.

213
00:08:30,598 --> 00:08:32,064
哈! 是啊
Ha! Yeah.

214
00:08:32,099 --> 00:08:33,199
哇哦
Wow.

215
00:08:33,233 --> 00:08:34,367
你也在这儿
There you are.

216
00:08:34,401 --> 00:08:35,768
你来干嘛?
What are you doing there?

217
00:08:35,803 --> 00:08:39,005
吉布斯探员派你担任瓦里斯案子的联络员
Agent Gibbs assigned you to be my liaison on the Wallace case.

218
00:08:39,039 --> 00:08:40,239
噢
Oh.

219
00:08:40,273 --> 00:08:42,074
联络员是什么意思? 
What do you mean, "liaison"?

220
00:08:42,109 --> 00:08:44,844
你现在是个记者
You're a reporter now.

221
00:08:44,879 --> 00:08:47,479
我们不需要...和记者联络
We don't... liaise with reporters.

222
00:08:47,514 --> 00:08:49,347
但是现在你必须这么做
You do now.

223
00:08:49,382 --> 00:08:51,349
吉布斯可没和我说起这事
Gibbs didn't say anything to me about this.

224
00:08:51,384 --> 00:08:53,051
嘿 托尼 托尼 托尼!
Hey, Tony, Tony, Tony!

225
00:08:53,085 --> 00:08:55,020
吉布斯让我转达你...
Gibbs wanted me to tell you that...

226
00:08:55,054 --> 00:08:58,524
噢 你好
Oh. Hello.

227
00:08:58,558 --> 00:08:59,992
你好
Hi.

228
00:09:00,026 --> 00:09:02,460
所以...
So...

229
00:09:03,328 --> 00:09:04,929
我们要怎么办?
what do we do now?

230
00:09:04,963 --> 00:09:06,898
托尼 我也对这件事很不满
Well, I'm not happy about it, either, Tony,

231
00:09:06,932 --> 00:09:08,407
但我希望你拿出你的专业精神来
but I expect you to be professional.

232
00:09:08,432 --> 00:09:09,066
我一直很敬业
Always.

233
00:09:09,067 --> 00:09:10,267
我们之间没必要搞得像敌人一样
It's not like we're enemies.

234
00:09:10,301 --> 00:09:13,237
对啊 我邀请你参加过圣诞聚餐
Exactly. I did invite you to Christmas brunch,

235
00:09:13,271 --> 00:09:15,640
而且我们曾经订了婚
and at one point in our lives, we were engaged to be married.

236
00:09:16,875 --> 00:09:19,042
太强悍了
Meow.

237
00:09:19,076 --> 00:09:21,110
我想再打个招呼...
Hi... again.

238
00:09:21,145 --> 00:09:22,679
我叫艾比
I'm Abby.

239
00:09:22,713 --> 00:09:23,847
我叫温迪
Wendy.

240
00:09:23,881 --> 00:09:25,048
温迪!
Wendy!

241
00:09:25,082 --> 00:09:27,617
那个前未婚妻 温迪
Wendy the ex-fiancée.

242
00:09:42,279 --> 00:09:43,479
麦基 他们来了 他们来了!
McGee, here they come, here they come!

243
00:09:43,504 --> 00:09:44,346
等等...
Hold on...

244
00:09:44,347 --> 00:09:46,281
头儿! 我们能不能谈一谈?
Boss! Can I talk to you for a second?

245
00:09:46,315 --> 00:09:49,117
噢 温迪 穿过那扇门 走到底
Uh, Wendy, conference room is just through that door,

246
00:09:49,152 --> 00:09:50,147
就是会议室 麻烦你先走
there at the end. Thanks.

247
00:09:50,148 --> 00:09:51,649
让我当温迪的联络员? 你想什么呢?
I'm Wendy's liaison? What were you thinking?

248
00:09:51,683 --> 00:09:54,552
你就跟她说事情有变 我...
You were there when it went south. I c...

249
00:09:54,586 --> 00:09:55,886
不行
Sorry.

250
00:09:57,288 --> 00:09:58,755
抱歉
Sorry.

251
00:10:19,342 --> 00:10:20,942
我们要专业地对待这事儿吧
Aren't we professional.

252
00:10:20,977 --> 00:10:23,011
当然
That's what we are.

253
00:10:23,045 --> 00:10:25,313
恩 我们从基本的开始
Okay, let's start with the basics.

254
00:10:25,348 --> 00:10:27,039
你以前和瓦里斯相识吗? 不
Have you ever spoken with Wallace before? no

255
00:10:27,550 --> 00:10:29,284
知道他为何在死前打给你?
Have any idea what his call was about?

256
00:10:29,318 --> 00:10:30,425
不知道
Nope.

257
00:10:30,450 --> 00:10:32,540
你为什么邀请我去圣诞聚餐?
Why'd you invite me to Christmas brunch?

258
00:10:32,688 --> 00:10:34,489
我以为看到你会很高兴
Thought it might be nice to see you.

259
00:10:34,523 --> 00:10:35,890
可能我错了
I may have been wrong.

260
00:10:37,393 --> 00:10:40,327
- 轮到我了 - 轮到你干嘛?
- My turn. - Your turn what?

261
00:10:40,362 --> 00:10:41,696
我要问几个问题
I get to ask some questions.

262
00:10:41,730 --> 00:10:43,163
那是我和旺斯的协议
That's my deal with Vance.

263
00:10:45,133 --> 00:10:47,434
瓦利斯上校有精神病史吗?
Does Captain Wallace have a history of mental illness?

264
00:10:47,435 --> 00:10:49,235
没有
No.

265
00:10:49,270 --> 00:10:52,305
那你们海军知道他在偷偷扮英雄吗?
Was the navy aware that he was moonlighting as a... Superhero?

266
00:10:52,339 --> 00:10:53,540
不知道
No.

267
00:10:53,574 --> 00:10:55,909
你什么时候开始穿上千元的西装?
Since when did you start wearing thousand-dollar suits?

268
00:10:55,943 --> 00:10:58,177
你什么时候不再教4岁的小孩子唱
Since when did you stop teaching four-year-olds how to sing

269
00:10:58,212 --> 00:11:00,881
神龙帕夫 继而转型成超人妻子?
"Puff the Magic Dragon" and start channeling Lois Lane?

270
00:11:00,915 --> 00:11:02,748
人总是会变的
People change.

271
00:11:02,783 --> 00:11:04,917
是啊 他们是的
Yes, they do.

272
00:11:04,951 --> 00:11:06,385
我没有错
I wasn't wrong.

273
00:11:06,420 --> 00:11:08,387
很高兴能见到你
It is nice to see you.

274
00:11:09,956 --> 00:11:11,924
我也是
It's nice to see you, too.

275
00:11:11,958 --> 00:11:13,659
恩
Mm.

276
00:11:18,665 --> 00:11:20,966
得了吧 这是我发明的
Come on. I invented that.

277
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:22,367
呃 我们来只是想跟你说
Well, we just wanted to let you know

278
00:11:22,402 --> 00:11:24,836
艾比还无法确定上传那个打架视频的
that Abby's still unable to identify the user

279
00:11:24,870 --> 00:11:25,904
用户的身份
who uploaded that fight video.

280
00:11:25,939 --> 00:11:27,139
噢
Oh.

281
00:11:27,173 --> 00:11:28,373
吉布斯希望我们调查下周围居民
Gibbs wants us to canvas the neighborhood.

282
00:11:28,408 --> 00:11:31,276
看有没有人认识那个酒鬼
See if anyone knows who the drunk idiot is.

283
00:11:31,311 --> 00:11:32,510
噢 那个人我不认识 但我知道那个视频
Oh, I don't know him, but that video

284
00:11:32,545 --> 00:11:34,446
是一个叫克莱恩斯・托百特的人拍的
was shot by a man name Clarence Tobett.

285
00:11:34,480 --> 00:11:35,546
本地信托基金的宠儿
Local trust-fund baby,

286
00:11:35,580 --> 00:11:37,748
经营反对帮派的业务
runs an anti-gang outreach program.

287
00:11:37,782 --> 00:11:39,116
- 我是个记者 - 记者
- Reporter. - Reporter.

288
00:11:39,151 --> 00:11:40,985
他总是会写一些东西
He's always calling the paper,

289
00:11:41,019 --> 00:11:42,686
以引起民众注意
trying to drum up publicity.

290
00:11:42,720 --> 00:11:43,921
谢谢
Thank you.

291
00:11:43,956 --> 00:11:45,957
恩 记得告诉我你们的新发现
Hm. Let me know what you find.

292
00:11:46,891 --> 00:11:48,993
她人很好啊
She is cute.

293
00:11:49,027 --> 00:11:50,261
打住
Stop it.

294
00:11:53,197 --> 00:11:56,399
你的前未婚妻很可爱啊
Your ex-fiancée's really cute.

295
00:11:56,434 --> 00:11:57,934
和我想的大相径庭啊
But I would expect no less.

296
00:11:57,969 --> 00:12:00,470
这么多年后相见 感觉很陌生吧?
Must be strange seeing her again after all these years, huh?

297
00:12:00,504 --> 00:12:01,704
尤其是在她离婚后?
Especially with her divorced?

298
00:12:03,407 --> 00:12:05,041
你居然不吭声
Almost as strange as you not talking.

299
00:12:05,076 --> 00:12:07,376
我在工作 你投入点 谢谢了
I'm working. You should try it. Thank you.

300
00:12:09,712 --> 00:12:11,280
你是克莱恩斯 托百特?
Clarence Tobett?

301
00:12:11,314 --> 00:12:12,481
你们是?
Who wants to know?

302
00:12:12,515 --> 00:12:14,984
海军罪案调查处!
NCIS!

303
00:12:15,018 --> 00:12:17,719
我们在找拍这段视频的人
We're looking for the man who shot this video.

304
00:12:22,925 --> 00:12:24,993
你们怎么找到我的?
How'd you find me?

305
00:12:25,027 --> 00:12:27,695
我花了好大劲儿隐藏身份
I work very hard to keep my true identity a secret.

306
00:12:27,729 --> 00:12:29,998
噢 咔嚓!
Oh, snap!

307
00:12:30,032 --> 00:12:32,933
你是他们中的一个!
You're one of them!

308
00:12:32,968 --> 00:12:35,769
如果你是指现实生活超级英雄 那就对了
If you mean Real-Life Superhero, then, yes.

309
00:12:36,872 --> 00:12:39,539
让我猜猜 你是ICU?
Let me guess. ICU?

310
00:12:39,573 --> 00:12:41,541
是 这也是你们过来
That's right, 'cause that's where you go

311
00:12:41,575 --> 00:12:42,809
调查我的原因吧
if you mess with me.

312
00:12:45,346 --> 00:12:47,114
鉴于我们...
Since we're...

313
00:12:47,148 --> 00:12:48,281
是同行
coworkers,

314
00:12:48,316 --> 00:12:49,649
我会充分配合你们
you will have my complete cooperation.

315
00:12:49,683 --> 00:12:51,151
是 是我拍了那段视频
Yes, I shot the video.

316
00:12:51,185 --> 00:12:53,953
我在当罪犯诱饵时遇到这起事件的
I came upon the fight when I was out on bait patrol.

317
00:12:53,988 --> 00:12:55,121
罪犯诱饵?
Bait patrol?

318
00:12:55,155 --> 00:12:58,090
对 一种专业的引诱打击罪犯的策略
Yes, it's a standard crime-fighting tactic.

319
00:12:58,125 --> 00:13:00,126
我们中的某个人...别 别 别
One of us... No, no, no, no, no, no.

320
00:13:00,160 --> 00:13:02,995
...扮成诱饵 等待
...acts as bait, and waits

321
00:13:03,030 --> 00:13:04,430
罪犯上钩
for someone to cause trouble.

322
00:13:04,464 --> 00:13:06,665
他们一旦有所行动 我们就进行反击
When they do, we give it to them.

323
00:13:06,699 --> 00:13:08,034
- 克莱恩斯! - 噢!
- Clarence! - Oh!

324
00:13:08,068 --> 00:13:10,569
我什么时候允许你把汤姆借走了?
What did I tell you about borrowing Tom?

325
00:13:10,603 --> 00:13:12,437
- 我... - 不!
- I... - No!

326
00:13:12,471 --> 00:13:13,505
不 不 不!
No, no, no!

327
00:13:13,539 --> 00:13:16,541
佩顿小姐说你们是NCIS的人
Miss Peyton said you're from NCIS.

328
00:13:16,575 --> 00:13:18,076
他犯了什么事?
What did he do now?

329
00:13:18,110 --> 00:13:19,344
爸 没事
Nothing, Dad.

330
00:13:19,378 --> 00:13:22,480
事实上 是你打断了我们 我们在说正事
In fact, if you'll excuse us, this is business.

331
00:13:22,515 --> 00:13:24,749
不 不 我在做的才叫正事
No, no. Business is what I do.

332
00:13:24,783 --> 00:13:26,384
而你只是在花我给你的钱而已
I buy real estate, you just take it up.

333
00:13:26,419 --> 00:13:29,086
25岁的人了还像5岁小孩一样!
Acting like you're five, instead of 25!

334
00:13:29,120 --> 00:13:30,954
他到底干了些什么?
What did he do?

335
00:13:30,988 --> 00:13:33,057
噢 他其实是在帮我指认这个人
Oh, he was actually helping us identify someone.

336
00:13:33,091 --> 00:13:34,391
我记得这个人
I remember him.

337
00:13:34,426 --> 00:13:36,593
虽然我不知道他的名字
I don't have a name,

338
00:13:36,627 --> 00:13:39,563
但他逃走的时候我记下了他的牌照
but I got his license plate when he fled.

339
00:13:39,597 --> 00:13:40,797
呃 部分车牌号
Well, some of it.

340
00:13:40,831 --> 00:13:43,732
够了 就此打住 不许再把汤姆借走!
All right, I've heard enough. No more Tom!

341
00:13:43,767 --> 00:13:46,001
他是个强手 不能来陪你浪费时间
The guy's got a Bronze Star, for Pete's sake.

342
00:13:46,036 --> 00:13:47,303
他才是真正的英雄
He's a real hero.

343
00:13:48,905 --> 00:13:51,006
他就是气我
He's just pissed because I refuse

344
00:13:51,041 --> 00:13:53,209
不接手家族产业
to go into the family business.

345
00:13:53,243 --> 00:13:55,044
我猜也是这样
I can relate.

346
00:13:56,046 --> 00:13:57,413
克莱恩斯?
Clarence?

347
00:13:57,448 --> 00:14:00,182
- 克莱恩斯! -干嘛?
- Clarence! - What?

348
00:14:00,216 --> 00:14:02,217
- 车牌号? - 噢
- License plate? - Oh.

349
00:14:04,687 --> 00:14:06,388
三个数字
Three numbers.

350
00:14:06,422 --> 00:14:09,458
超强记忆该不会是你的超级能力吧
I guess super memory isn't one of your superpowers.

351
00:14:09,492 --> 00:14:13,228
随你取笑 但我做的事是正紧事
Make all the fun you want, but what I do is important.

352
00:14:13,262 --> 00:14:15,963
上个礼拜我成功说服一个孩子脱离犯罪组织
I talked a kid out of a gang just last week.

353
00:14:15,997 --> 00:14:18,799
我知道我们的服装很傻逼 但这只是个噱头而已
I know the costumes seem silly, but they're just a gimmick.

354
00:14:18,833 --> 00:14:20,934
服装是为了缓解紧张的气氛
They help defuse tense situations.

355
00:14:20,969 --> 00:14:23,537
我不知道Code队长的真实身份
Look, I don't know Captain Code's true identity.

356
00:14:23,572 --> 00:14:26,273
我觉得我们还是继续让它是个谜比较好
It's best that we keep them secret, even from each other,

357
00:14:26,308 --> 00:14:28,609
我听到了一些关于他的流言
but I did hear a rumor that something happened to him.

358
00:14:28,643 --> 00:14:30,444
不知道会不会对你们有帮助
I don't know if this helps you, but

359
00:14:30,479 --> 00:14:32,312
他说他遇到了情况
he had mentioned that he was onto something.

360
00:14:32,346 --> 00:14:34,214
不过没说清楚是什么事 反正...
He didn't say what, but it...

361
00:14:34,248 --> 00:14:36,216
他很担心
had him worried.

362
00:14:36,250 --> 00:14:38,050
这是我的名片
Here's my card.

363
00:14:38,085 --> 00:14:39,919
如果你们想要那种t恤的话
I have T-shirts, too,

364
00:14:39,953 --> 00:14:42,021
我也有
if you want them.

365
00:14:42,055 --> 00:14:43,423
谢谢 谢谢你了
Thank you. Thank you.

366
00:14:43,457 --> 00:14:44,924
恩
Mm-hmm.

367
00:14:48,128 --> 00:14:51,930
我年轻那会 也有真实生活中的超级英雄
We had our own real-life superhero in my youth.

368
00:14:51,964 --> 00:14:56,568
他把自己叫做The Fox 是个最早的环境学家的名字
He called himself "The Fox," one of the first environmentalists.

369
00:14:56,603 --> 00:14:59,704
有一次 他从污水区
Once, he collected 50 gallons of sewage

370
00:14:59,739 --> 00:15:03,241
收集了50加仑的废水
that was destroying a lake, broke into the...

371
00:15:03,275 --> 00:15:05,476
把它们泼到了
the offending corporation's offices,

372
00:15:05,511 --> 00:15:07,077
排出这些污水公司的办公大厅
and dumped it in their lobby.

373
00:15:08,514 --> 00:15:10,981
每个小孩都在幻想能快点长大
Every child fantasizes about growing up

374
00:15:11,016 --> 00:15:13,251
变成一个超级英雄
and becoming a superhero,

375
00:15:13,285 --> 00:15:15,052
但是你确实做到了
but you actually did it.

376
00:15:15,086 --> 00:15:17,955
真厉害啊
Impressive.

377
00:15:17,989 --> 00:15:19,956
达克 我可不会这么夸他
Not the word I would have chosen, Duck.

378
00:15:19,990 --> 00:15:21,291
你查到了什么?
What do you got?

379
00:15:21,325 --> 00:15:23,726
呃 我觉得这两个人应该是
Uh, I think we can assume that both victims

380
00:15:23,761 --> 00:15:25,094
死于枪杀
died of their gunshot wounds.

381
00:15:25,129 --> 00:15:26,396
这很显然
Not surprised.

382
00:15:26,430 --> 00:15:28,365
是啊 让人意外的是我在瓦里斯上校
Yeah, well, the surprise came

383
00:15:28,399 --> 00:15:32,335
身上发现的伤口数量
from the number of injuries I found on Captain Wallace.

384
00:15:32,370 --> 00:15:33,903
他的下巴被打伤两次
He broke his jaw twice.

385
00:15:33,937 --> 00:15:36,572
有多处刀伤
He has scars from numerous knife wounds

386
00:15:36,606 --> 00:15:38,674
甚至有枪弹的擦痕
and even has a bullet graze.

387
00:15:38,708 --> 00:15:39,741
他在街头打斗过
Doing a little street fighting.

388
00:15:39,776 --> 00:15:41,076
是啊 大概吧
Yeah, well, presumably.

389
00:15:41,110 --> 00:15:44,180
他很认真地在做保卫工作
He took his role as a vigilante quite seriously.

390
00:15:44,214 --> 00:15:45,747
拜托 达克
Come on, Duck.

391
00:15:45,782 --> 00:15:48,184
我想你应该不认同他们的做法吧?
I take it, you do not approve?

392
00:15:48,218 --> 00:15:49,485
达克 这不是他们该做的事
Duck, it's not their job.

393
00:15:49,519 --> 00:15:50,519
他们有可能会受伤
They could get hurt.

394
00:15:50,554 --> 00:15:53,454
杰瑟罗 他们大多数都受伤了
Jethro, most of them already have been.

395
00:15:53,489 --> 00:15:56,524
这些打击罪犯的人除了爱看漫画
Aside from their...their love of comic books,

396
00:15:56,559 --> 00:15:58,726
还有个共性 他们愿意
what most of these crime-fighters have in common

397
00:15:58,760 --> 00:16:01,496
牺牲自己
is being victims of violent crime themselves.

398
00:16:01,530 --> 00:16:02,997
付出名誉或是生命
Or abuse or tragedy.

399
00:16:03,031 --> 00:16:06,867
你看看瓦里斯上校的资料
I mean, take a look at Captain Wallace.

400
00:16:06,902 --> 00:16:08,868
他妻子在分娩时死亡
His wife died in childbirth.

401
00:16:08,903 --> 00:16:13,670
之后 她的女儿在购物商场遭遇天台塌陷而死
And then, his daughter died when a balcony collapsed in a shopping mall.

402
00:16:13,974 --> 00:16:17,010
麦基说他可是违反建筑条例的老手
McGee said his specialty was building-code violations.

403
00:16:17,044 --> 00:16:19,045
这可不是巧合
Well, hardly a coincidence.

404
00:16:19,080 --> 00:16:23,416
然而有一些人会选择陷入忧郁
Whereas others might have succumbed to depression or...

405
00:16:23,450 --> 00:16:28,153
或者滥用毒品 而这些人却把内心的忧虑
or drug abuse, these men and women have channeled their angst

406
00:16:28,188 --> 00:16:29,422
转化为积极的思绪
into something positive.

407
00:16:29,456 --> 00:16:31,190
谁能来做评价呢?
Who's to judge?

408
00:16:31,225 --> 00:16:35,261
但有件事我可能要对你做评价
Though the one thing I might judge you on

409
00:16:35,295 --> 00:16:40,232
那就是你让托尼担任新闻媒体的联系员
is your choice of Tony as liaison to the press.

410
00:16:40,466 --> 00:16:42,967
你在打算着什么 杰瑟罗?
What are you up to, Jethro?

411
00:16:43,001 --> 00:16:44,902
谢谢你 谢谢你 
Thank you. Thank you. Thank you.

412
00:16:44,937 --> 00:16:46,771
你们可以不用鼓掌了
You can all hold your applause.

413
00:16:46,805 --> 00:16:48,373
我们为啥可以不用鼓掌了?
For what are we not applauding?

414
00:16:48,407 --> 00:16:52,744
我发现了与花店保险箱上吻合的指纹
I got a hit on the DNA from the flower-shop safe.

415
00:16:52,778 --> 00:16:55,512
他叫菲利克斯 昆提罗
His name is Felix Quintero.

416
00:16:55,547 --> 00:16:56,647
曾做过街头小太保
He was a small-time hood

417
00:16:56,681 --> 00:16:58,349
但现在已经洗手不干了
but seems to have cleaned up his act.

418
00:16:58,383 --> 00:16:59,683
那他现在呢?
So, what's he doing now?

419
00:16:59,718 --> 00:17:01,084
好好听着吧
You're gonna love this.

420
00:17:01,119 --> 00:17:02,353
锁匠
Locksmith

421
00:17:02,387 --> 00:17:05,222
他的车牌和你从ICU那里得知的相符合
His license plate matches the partial you got from ICU.

422
00:17:05,257 --> 00:17:07,023
看起来他就是那位醉酒傻子
Looks like he's our drunk idiot.

423
00:17:07,058 --> 00:17:08,225
把他带来
Pick him up

424
00:17:08,260 --> 00:17:09,460
这就去
on it

425
00:17:15,766 --> 00:17:18,000
这案子或许马上就能结了
This case may be wrapping up soon.

426
00:17:18,034 --> 00:17:19,835
你就不能再见到你的前任了
You will be free from your ex.

427
00:17:19,870 --> 00:17:21,137
我很好 姬娃
I am fine, zive

428
00:17:21,171 --> 00:17:23,005
你看起来可不好啊
You do not seem fine.

429
00:17:23,039 --> 00:17:24,940
你看起来...忧郁啊
You seem... pensive.

430
00:17:24,975 --> 00:17:27,576
那是因为我早上吃了辣椒
It's the chili I had for breakfast this morning.

431
00:17:27,610 --> 00:17:29,944
你知道吗 你还从没和我讲过
You know, you have never actually told me how

432
00:17:29,979 --> 00:17:31,647
你俩是怎么结束的
it ended between you two.

433
00:17:34,651 --> 00:17:36,485
好了 当我没问
Okay, forget I asked.

434
00:17:36,519 --> 00:17:37,919
我们被跟踪了
We're being followed.

435
00:17:37,953 --> 00:17:39,954
我有很不好的预感
I had a feeling, a pensive one.

436
00:17:39,989 --> 00:17:41,523
刚才的掉头也证实了这点
U-turn confirmed it.

437
00:17:42,725 --> 00:17:44,057
行动吧
Let's move.

438
00:17:45,327 --> 00:17:47,127
NCIS 双手放方向盘上
NCIS! Hands on the wheel!

439
00:17:47,162 --> 00:17:48,629
嘿 注意点
Hey, watch out!

440
00:17:48,664 --> 00:17:50,631
怎么回事啊?
What is going on?

441
00:17:50,666 --> 00:17:52,400
嗨 俩位
Hi, guys.

442
00:17:52,434 --> 00:17:54,335
今天是个驾车的好日子 哈?
Great day for a drive, huh?

443
00:17:54,369 --> 00:17:55,703
你在干什么呢?
What are you doing?

444
00:17:55,737 --> 00:17:56,570
跟踪线索
Tracking down a lead.

445
00:17:56,605 --> 00:17:58,138
不 我俩才是在跟踪线索
No, we're tracking down a lead.

446
00:17:58,173 --> 00:17:59,439
你是在跟踪我们
You're following us.

447
00:17:59,473 --> 00:18:00,607
什么?难道这犯法吗
What? Is that a crime?

448
00:18:00,641 --> 00:18:01,908
是啊!
Yes!

449
00:18:01,942 --> 00:18:03,242
- 准确来说 是的 - 托尼
- Technically, it is. - Tony.

450
00:18:03,277 --> 00:18:05,345
听着 我只是确认能了解第一手信息
Look, I am just making sure I'm in the loop.

451
00:18:05,379 --> 00:18:07,084
我说了会告诉你进展的
I told you that I would let you know.

452
00:18:07,682 --> 00:18:09,916
只能说你这承诺这方面
Let's just say you don't have the best track record,

453
00:18:09,950 --> 00:18:11,618
做得确实不怎么好
doing the things you say you're gonna do.

454
00:18:11,652 --> 00:18:13,453
说我 你开玩笑吗?
Me?! Are you kidding?

455
00:18:18,391 --> 00:18:20,292
我打给消防署吧
I'll call the fire department.

456
00:18:20,327 --> 00:18:22,561
你的车都不喜欢你
Even your car doesn't like you.

457
00:18:23,463 --> 00:18:24,630
我才买的啊
I just got that car.

458
00:18:24,664 --> 00:18:26,332
不可能不喜欢我的
It hasn't had a chance not to like me.

459
00:18:26,366 --> 00:18:29,468
车也许喜欢你 可有人并不喜欢
Well, your car may like you, but someone does not.

460
00:18:31,537 --> 00:18:33,471
炸弹被接入燃油管道
It's a bomb wired into the fuel line,

461
00:18:33,505 --> 00:18:35,640
在车速驶入50码是自动引爆
timed to go off when the car hit 50.

462
00:18:35,674 --> 00:18:37,342
纸板做得

463
00:18:37,376 --> 00:18:39,543
没错 所以证据会被烧成灰烬
Yeah, so the evidence would burn in the crash,

464
00:18:39,577 --> 00:18:41,078
但制作很匆忙
but it was a rush job.

465
00:18:41,112 --> 00:18:42,512
温迪突然刹车
Wendy's quick stop

466
00:18:42,547 --> 00:18:44,781
导致其松散 加快了
jarred it loose, and the accelerant leaked

467
00:18:44,816 --> 00:18:45,916
它接入燃油系统的速率
onto the fuel block,

468
00:18:45,951 --> 00:18:47,885
之后便着火 她真幸运的
making it catch on fire. Lucky for her.

469
00:18:47,919 --> 00:18:49,453
幸运 艾比 有人想杀了她
Lucky, Abbs? Someone was trying to kill her.

470
00:18:49,487 --> 00:18:51,088
我只是试着乐观点嘛
I'm just trying to be positive.

471
00:18:51,122 --> 00:18:52,890
嘿 准不定是托尼
Hey, maybe it was Tony.

472
00:18:52,924 --> 00:18:54,191
没那可能性
Not positive.

473
00:18:54,226 --> 00:18:56,025
我们找出了更多的信息
Afraid we got a little more of that.

474
00:18:56,060 --> 00:18:57,126
我们发现了这个
We found this.

475
00:18:57,161 --> 00:18:58,561
温迪的笔笔记
It's Wendy's notes.

476
00:18:58,595 --> 00:19:01,630
一些是这个案子的 但还有一些是从
From our current case, but there's also some stuff from

477
00:19:01,665 --> 00:19:03,432
有关她的报纸上截取的
old newspaper stories of hers.

478
00:19:03,467 --> 00:19:05,835
还记得她说过不认识瓦里斯上校吗?
Remember she said she didn't know Captain Wallace?

479
00:19:05,870 --> 00:19:07,503
恩
Yeah.

480
00:19:07,537 --> 00:19:08,838
根据她的笔记
Well, according to her notes,

481
00:19:08,873 --> 00:19:11,006
她曾和他一起合作过几次
she's worked with him several times in the past.

482
00:19:11,040 --> 00:19:12,774
意味着...
Which means...

483
00:19:12,808 --> 00:19:15,077
她骗了我们
She lied to us.

484
00:19:21,118 --> 00:19:23,119
米勒小姐 我只问你一遍
Miss Miller, I'm only gonna ask you once.

485
00:19:23,154 --> 00:19:24,755
你和瓦里斯上校相识多久了?
How long did you know Captain Wallace?

486
00:19:24,789 --> 00:19:25,922
讲过了 我不认识他
I told you, I didn't.

487
00:19:25,957 --> 00:19:28,859
根据你的笔记 之前你报导过三则新闻
According to your files, he was a source

488
00:19:28,893 --> 00:19:30,994
而他正是消息来源
on three prior news articles of yours.

489
00:19:31,028 --> 00:19:32,796
我是个记者 而这些是特权文件
I am a reporter! These are privileged documents!

490
00:19:32,831 --> 00:19:35,231
你没有权利看我的笔记
You have no right to look through my notes.

491
00:19:35,265 --> 00:19:36,399
你的笔记
Your notes

492
00:19:36,433 --> 00:19:38,300
正是这起谋杀案件的证据 温迪
are evidence in an attempted murder, Wendy.

493
00:19:38,335 --> 00:19:39,802
谋杀你的案件
Yours.

494
00:19:47,277 --> 00:19:50,979
我只是在揭露有关浪费军方开支的报道
I was doing an expose on wasteful military spending.

495
00:19:51,013 --> 00:19:52,146
瓦里斯当时提供线索
Wallace was a source.

496
00:19:52,181 --> 00:19:53,615
如果告诉你们我认识他
If I told you I knew him,

497
00:19:53,649 --> 00:19:54,949
你们肯定会查出来的
you'd figure that out.

498
00:19:54,984 --> 00:19:56,651
记者不能揭露他们的线人 不管他生死与否
Reporters do not reveal their sources, dead or alive.

499
00:19:56,686 --> 00:19:59,087
她说实话了没 蒂诺佐探员?
Is she telling the truth, Agent DiNozzo?

500
00:20:00,890 --> 00:20:02,791
抱歉 什么?
I'm sorry. What?

501
00:20:02,825 --> 00:20:04,993
我刚得知你和米勒女士的情史
Just found out about your history with Miss Miller.

502
00:20:05,027 --> 00:20:07,795
有关这个我们稍后详谈
And we'll talk about that later.

503
00:20:07,829 --> 00:20:09,630
我想你也许能辨认出来
I figured you might have some incite.

504
00:20:09,664 --> 00:20:11,965
哦 呃..
Oh. Um...

505
00:20:14,903 --> 00:20:16,437
是
Yeah.

506
00:20:16,471 --> 00:20:17,838
她说的都是真的
She's... she's telling the truth.

507
00:20:17,873 --> 00:20:20,140
瓦里斯死之前为何会打给你?
Why did Wallace call you before he was killed?

508
00:20:20,174 --> 00:20:22,475
我想他可能又有什么线索
Well, I assumed he had a lead on another story.

509
00:20:22,510 --> 00:20:23,743
但我真的不知道
But I really don't know.

510
00:20:23,778 --> 00:20:25,612
这我没说假话
I-I didn't lie about that.

511
00:20:25,646 --> 00:20:26,746
你肯定知道什么内幕
Well, you obviously know something.

512
00:20:26,781 --> 00:20:28,347
有人想谋杀你
There was an attempt on your life.

513
00:20:28,382 --> 00:20:30,249
我发现了 有嫌疑的人吗?
I noticed. You got a suspect?

514
00:20:30,284 --> 00:20:31,818
我们对他的公寓实行监视
We're staking out his apartment.

515
00:20:31,852 --> 00:20:33,252
直到我们找到他 我们可以...
Until we find him, we can...

516
00:20:33,287 --> 00:20:34,521
对我实行保护性监护
Place me in protective custody.

517
00:20:34,555 --> 00:20:36,689
让我进可能地不要插手此事?
And keep me as far away from this story as possible?

518
00:20:36,724 --> 00:20:38,057
不可能
Forget it.

519
00:20:38,091 --> 00:20:39,958
我有藏身的地方 我会没事的
I got a place to lay low. I'll be fine.

520
00:20:39,992 --> 00:20:41,993
这我相信 但我
I don't doubt that,, but I'm going to have

521
00:20:42,028 --> 00:20:43,295
还是坚持
to insist on sending an agent

522
00:20:43,329 --> 00:20:45,063
派遣一个探员送你回去
to escort you to your destination.

523
00:20:45,097 --> 00:20:46,298
蒂诺佐探员
Agent DiNozzo,

524
00:20:46,332 --> 00:20:47,999
考虑你俩的关系 你要愿意
given the circumstances, if you'd like,

525
00:20:48,034 --> 00:20:49,601
我可以派戴维探员
I can assign Agent David.

526
00:20:49,636 --> 00:20:51,537
不可能
No way in hell.

527
00:20:55,741 --> 00:20:57,909
没事的 我搞得定
It's ok. I got it.

528
00:20:59,645 --> 00:21:01,145
你渴了?
You thirsty?

529
00:21:01,179 --> 00:21:02,980
要吃点什么吗?
Can I get you something to eat?

530
00:21:03,014 --> 00:21:04,682
我不饿
Not hungry.

531
00:21:04,716 --> 00:21:06,350
你什么时候会不饿了?
Since when are you not hungry?

532
00:21:06,384 --> 00:21:09,019
人都有不饿的时候
People get not hungry. It happens.

533
00:21:09,054 --> 00:21:11,154
对你来说 才不是
Not to you, it doesn't.

534
00:21:11,188 --> 00:21:13,457
好了 我看得出来
Okay, I can tell.

535
00:21:13,491 --> 00:21:15,525
你有事想说
There is something on your mind.

536
00:21:17,428 --> 00:21:19,629
你还在因为我跟踪你那事生气啊
Are you still pissed at me because I followed you?

537
00:21:19,664 --> 00:21:22,031
没 只是对你笔记里一些事深感好奇
