00:28:14,017 --> 00:28:15,718
呃 我觉得他喜欢你
Hm. I think he likes you.

731
00:28:15,752 --> 00:28:17,486
哼
Hmm.

732
00:28:25,128 --> 00:28:27,296
好吧 我准备好听了
Okay, let's hear it.

733
00:28:27,331 --> 00:28:28,931
听什么?
Hear what?

734
00:28:28,966 --> 00:28:30,531
我确定她肯定说了什么
I'm sure she said something.

735
00:28:30,566 --> 00:28:32,800
有什么值得告诉我的内幕?
Is there something to tell?

736
00:28:37,006 --> 00:28:38,439
哦
Oh.

737
00:28:43,079 --> 00:28:46,247
哦 我看得出来 咱俩还是很像的
Oh, I can see you and I are a lot alike.

738
00:28:48,149 --> 00:28:51,818
大男人的行为 寡言少语
Both men of action, few words.

739
00:28:58,826 --> 00:29:00,594
杰克・瓦里斯上校
Captain Jack Wallace.

740
00:29:02,162 --> 00:29:04,430
德克斯特・墨菲
Dexter Murphy.

741
00:29:04,464 --> 00:29:07,333
罪案现场找到了你的DNA
Your DNA was found at the crime scene.

742
00:29:07,368 --> 00:29:10,636
电话回复机上也出现了你威胁的话语
And your voice was on the answering machine making threats.

743
00:29:10,670 --> 00:29:12,738
你认为我的凶手
You think I'm the killer?

744
00:29:14,508 --> 00:29:15,875
太荒谬了!
This is nuts!

745
00:29:15,910 --> 00:29:17,810
为什么我要杀死
Why on Earth-616 would I kill

746
00:29:17,844 --> 00:29:20,312
自己的超级英雄同伴?
my fellow superheroes?

747
00:29:23,116 --> 00:29:25,550
我可不想惹上麻烦 你不想惹麻烦?
I don't want any trouble! You don't want any trouble?

748
00:29:25,584 --> 00:29:27,052
不! 真糟糕 是你找到的
No! Too bad 'cause you found it!

749
00:29:27,086 --> 00:29:29,922
你个傻子 是你找到的! 让他走吧!
No, punk, you found it! Let him go!

750
00:29:29,956 --> 00:29:31,123
很欣赏你的诚实
Appreciate the honesty.

751
00:29:31,157 --> 00:29:33,591
实际上 温迪也这么说你的
Actually, that is something Wendy mentioned about you.

752
00:29:33,626 --> 00:29:38,029
你是她所认识的最诚实的人呢
That you were one of the most honest people she knew.

753
00:29:38,063 --> 00:29:39,898
真的吗?
Really?

754
00:29:41,366 --> 00:29:42,667
对别人很诚实
To others.

755
00:29:42,701 --> 00:29:44,936
她说你只对自己会撒谎
She said the only person you lie to is yourself.

756
00:29:44,970 --> 00:29:47,806
而且还是经常性的
Which she says you do a lot.

757
00:29:47,840 --> 00:29:49,273
哈 这个...
Huh, well...

758
00:29:51,976 --> 00:29:53,143
精彩爆了
That was awesome.

759
00:29:53,177 --> 00:29:54,978
但你却想错了
But you got it all wrong.

760
00:29:55,012 --> 00:29:56,914
这段录像是安排好的
That video was staged.

761
00:29:56,948 --> 00:29:59,349
Code和Solanum队长雇我安排的那出袭击
Captain Code and Solanum hired me to fake that attack.

762
00:29:59,383 --> 00:30:00,684
没人知道 甚至录像师
Nobody knew, not even the cameraman.

763
00:30:00,718 --> 00:30:01,685
为什么?
Why?

764
00:30:01,719 --> 00:30:02,786
宣传啊 知道不
Publicity, duh.

765
00:30:02,821 --> 00:30:04,788
他们想成立自己的超级英雄团
They wanted to start their own superhero league.

766
00:30:04,823 --> 00:30:06,356
如今大家伙都有自己的团了
Everyone's got a league these days;

767
00:30:06,390 --> 00:30:08,825
团结社区什么的
there's a unity in the community.

768
00:30:08,859 --> 00:30:10,292
多好的名字啊
That's a great league name.

769
00:30:10,327 --> 00:30:11,828
团结社区
Unity in the Community.

770
00:30:11,862 --> 00:30:13,563
我喜欢莱文沃思
I like Leavenworth.

771
00:30:13,597 --> 00:30:17,433
这样的 他们至今还没给我雇佣费
Look, they never paid me for the video.

772
00:30:17,468 --> 00:30:19,502
我也不知道他们真名
And I didn't know their real names,

773
00:30:19,536 --> 00:30:22,071
所以我就查了下 留下那短信
so I tracked them down, and I left that message.

774
00:30:22,105 --> 00:30:23,905
然后就去要回我的钱
Then I came back later to get my money.

775
00:30:23,940 --> 00:30:26,107
瓦里斯和墨菲早已死了
Wallace and Murphy were already dead.

776
00:30:26,141 --> 00:30:27,742
没错
Yep.

777
00:30:27,777 --> 00:30:29,210
然后 你就洗劫了那地
So, you robbed the place.

778
00:30:29,244 --> 00:30:31,245
准确地说 那钱是属于我的
Technically, the money I took was mine.

779
00:30:31,280 --> 00:30:34,983
嘿 知道我为啥自封Soulless(灵魂缺失者)
Hey, why do you think I call myself Soulless?

780
00:30:35,017 --> 00:30:37,452
但 我不是什么杀手
But... I am not a killer.

781
00:30:37,487 --> 00:30:40,087
我留下那通语音时人还没到城里
I was halfway across town when I left that voice mail,

782
00:30:40,121 --> 00:30:42,222
Toln退休中心那有50个人
and there's 50 gramass at Toln Retirement Center

783
00:30:42,256 --> 00:30:43,624
可以为我作证呢
that can vouch for me.

784
00:30:43,658 --> 00:30:45,793
我谁也没杀
I didn't kill anybody.

785
00:30:53,604 --> 00:30:56,239
退休中心的管理主任
Well, the administrator at the retirement center

786
00:30:56,274 --> 00:30:57,673
确实了昆提罗不在场的证据
confirmed Quintero's alibi.

787
00:30:57,707 --> 00:31:00,342
Soulless在星期二晚上参加了一个魔术表演
Soulless does a magic show for the residents on Tuesday nights.

788
00:31:00,377 --> 00:31:02,311
他不是我们要找的人
He's not our guy.

789
00:31:02,345 --> 00:31:03,946
我们该看看其他的超级英雄们
We should look at other superheroes.

790
00:31:03,980 --> 00:31:05,347
呃 也许有人嫉妒
Uh, maybe someone was getting jealous

791
00:31:05,382 --> 00:31:06,782
瓦里斯所得的光彩
of all the attention Wallace was getting.

792
00:31:06,816 --> 00:31:07,783
调查记者的档案
Link was the reporter.

793
00:31:07,817 --> 00:31:08,917
我不知道 头儿
Well, I don't know, boss.

794
00:31:08,952 --> 00:31:10,919
我想的是其他一些天使们
I can think of a bunch of other angles.

795
00:31:12,489 --> 00:31:14,989
好吧 这档案是咱们那位记者的
Okay, the link is the reporter.

796
00:31:15,023 --> 00:31:16,291
来继续谈谈她吧
Let's keep talking about her.

797
00:31:16,325 --> 00:31:17,658
我们知道她参与了
We know she was working on

798
00:31:17,693 --> 00:31:19,094
几次告密者活动
several whistle- blower stories

799
00:31:19,128 --> 00:31:20,161
和瓦里斯一起
with Wallace.

800
00:31:20,196 --> 00:31:21,796
也许他们揭发的信息有误
Well, maybe they blew the wrong whistle.

801
00:31:21,830 --> 00:31:23,531
或者打算揭露个不一样的内幕
Or were about to blow a different one.

802
00:31:23,566 --> 00:31:25,066
温迪说瓦里斯在他死的前一天
Wendy said that Wallace called her

803
00:31:25,101 --> 00:31:26,601
给她打了电话
the day before he was killed.

804
00:31:26,635 --> 00:31:28,136
可能是他发现了一些新的线索
Perhaps he was onto something new.

805
00:31:28,170 --> 00:31:29,769
姬娃 再去联系下他的指挥官
Ziva, talk to his C.O. again.

806
00:31:29,804 --> 00:31:31,004
麦基 把有关她的那些新闻找来
McGee, get me those old news stories.

807
00:31:31,038 --> 00:31:32,639
我会整合成一个文件
I'll put together a file.

808
00:31:32,673 --> 00:31:34,241
蒂诺佐
DiNozzo.

809
00:31:34,275 --> 00:31:35,976
知道 检查温迪的电话记录
I know. Go through Wendy's phone records

810
00:31:36,010 --> 00:31:37,744
然后联系那些在过去的六个月里
and talk to every guy she's spoken with

811
00:31:37,778 --> 00:31:38,912
跟她说过话的每一个人
in the last six months.

812
00:31:38,946 --> 00:31:40,380
不是 我已经弄了
No. I got that.

813
00:31:40,415 --> 00:31:42,082
达克打来了 下楼去 看看他想要些什么
Ducky called. Go down, see what he wants.

814
00:31:42,117 --> 00:31:43,517
谢谢你 头儿
Thank you, boss.

815
00:31:47,154 --> 00:31:48,221
你好
Hello.

816
00:31:48,255 --> 00:31:49,555
我还以为吉布斯会来
I was expecting Gibbs.

817
00:31:49,590 --> 00:31:50,756
他让我来
He sent me.

818
00:31:50,790 --> 00:31:51,991
你发现了什么
What do you got?

819
00:31:52,025 --> 00:31:57,000
恩 我给其他验尸员发了有关
Well, I've been e-mailing a few fellow M.E.s

820
00:31:57,264 --> 00:31:58,598
这案例的邮件
about our case.

821
00:31:58,632 --> 00:32:00,899
他们提供了一些有关系的信息
They've provided some pertinent information.

822
00:32:00,934 --> 00:32:04,836
很难相信他们有时候会这么小
Hard to believe they're so small sometimes.

823
00:32:04,870 --> 00:32:06,571
托尼 你在想些什么
What's on your mind, Tony?

824
00:32:06,606 --> 00:32:08,306
你有点愁眉苦脸的
You sound a little pensive.

825
00:32:08,341 --> 00:32:10,142
我没有
I am not pensive!

826
00:32:10,176 --> 00:32:12,977
为什么每个人都这样说 我
What is it with everyone and that word?! I...

827
00:32:13,879 --> 00:32:15,380
不好意思
Sorry.

828
00:32:15,414 --> 00:32:16,314
我只是
I'm just...

829
00:32:16,349 --> 00:32:19,049
你介不介意谈一下
Would you care to talk about it?

830
00:32:22,320 --> 00:32:24,555
你有没有遇到过很恐怖的事 然后你觉得
You ever had something terrible happen and then you think

831
00:32:24,589 --> 00:32:27,191
你早已将其置之身后 但恐惧又再次出现
you put it all behind you, but then the terrible comes back

832
00:32:27,225 --> 00:32:29,160
并且变得比以前更加令人害怕
and it's more terrible than it was before?

833
00:32:29,194 --> 00:32:31,529
我现在很困扰
I'm confused.

834
00:32:31,563 --> 00:32:32,763
我也是
So am I.

835
00:32:32,797 --> 00:32:36,732
托尼 从认识你的第一天
Tony, it was very clear to me from the very first day

836
00:32:36,767 --> 00:32:40,303
我就深知你是个情场曲折的人
that I met you that you were a man in pain.

837
00:32:40,337 --> 00:32:42,205
对不起 我觉得你把我
I'm sorry, I think you have me

838
00:32:42,239 --> 00:32:43,273
跟别人弄混了
confused with someone else.

839
00:32:43,307 --> 00:32:45,975
不 在我看来 你的痛苦和杰瑟罗一样
No, your pain was as clear to me as Jethro's.

840
00:32:46,009 --> 00:32:48,244
他失去了莎侬 他一生的挚爱
He lost Shannon, the one love of his life,

841
00:32:48,279 --> 00:32:52,047
而你则是因纷繁复杂的原因失去了信仰
and you lost faith in yourself for so many reasons.

842
00:32:52,081 --> 00:32:54,816
杰瑟罗选择不停地和别人结婚
Jethro coped with his pain by

843
00:32:54,850 --> 00:32:56,885
来掩埋这份痛楚
repeatedly marrying the wrong woman,

844
00:32:56,919 --> 00:32:59,788
这也造成他最终会孤身一人的结局
thus insuring that ultimately he would be alone

845
00:32:59,822 --> 00:33:01,690
并且永远心痛
and safe from heartbreak.

846
00:33:01,724 --> 00:33:05,160
你是重复地追逐错误的对象
You repeatedly chase the wrong woman.

847
00:33:05,194 --> 00:33:10,031
你现在很孤独是因为 你没能做到 如你所说
You're alone because you never did, as you just said,

848
00:33:10,265 --> 00:33:12,866
将其抛之于脑后
put it all behind you.

849
00:33:18,039 --> 00:33:19,373
当温迪在结婚前一夜
When Wendy told me the night before

850
00:33:19,408 --> 00:33:21,774
告诉我取消婚礼时
we were supposed to get married that she was calling it off,

851
00:33:21,809 --> 00:33:23,042
我完全不能接受
I didn't take it very well.

852
00:33:23,077 --> 00:33:26,246
我们有九年都没有说过话了
We hadn't spoken in nine years,

853
00:33:26,280 --> 00:33:28,281
直到昨天
until yesterday.

854
00:33:28,316 --> 00:33:32,719
好了 也许命运在给你一个去完结的机会
Well, perhaps fate has given you another chance at closure.

855
00:33:32,753 --> 00:33:35,522
又或者其他
Or something else.

856
00:33:35,556 --> 00:33:38,257
不是命运 是吉布斯
It's not fate, it's Gibbs.

857
00:33:38,291 --> 00:33:40,092
他在整我
Dude set me up.

858
00:33:41,961 --> 00:33:44,463
验尸官说了什么
What did the M.E. have to say?

859
00:33:44,497 --> 00:33:46,765
我们交流了一下
Uh, we exchanged notes on

860
00:33:46,799 --> 00:33:49,668
这些超级英雄的生活动向
the Real-Life Superhero movement.

861
00:33:49,703 --> 00:33:51,069
结果是
It turns out,

862
00:33:51,104 --> 00:33:54,472
这家伙于几个月前在临近的街区被人杀害
one was killed in the next district several months ago.

863
00:33:54,506 --> 00:33:57,108
我做了一些调查 发现另一起也是谋杀
I did some checking and found another was murdered

864
00:33:57,142 --> 00:33:58,776
而且时间还更早
sometime before that.

865
00:33:58,810 --> 00:34:00,911
因此 这些要么是
Ergo, either these are the result

866
00:34:00,946 --> 00:34:04,849
由于高危工作造成的 或者
of a very dangerous line of work or...

867
00:34:04,883 --> 00:34:07,218
有人杀了超级英雄么
Somebody's killing Superheroes?

868
00:34:09,520 --> 00:34:10,754
说吧
Talk to me.

869
00:34:10,788 --> 00:34:13,056
我们汇编整理了下机器谋杀案件的资料
We compiled the case data on the different murders.

870
00:34:13,090 --> 00:34:15,191
4个受害者 三个罪案现场
Four victims, three crime scenes.

871
00:34:15,226 --> 00:34:17,461
首先 这看起来并没有可以考察的地方 亲们
At first, it looks like nothing to see here, folks.

872
00:34:17,495 --> 00:34:19,296
目击者声称前两名受害者
The witnesses said that the first two victims

873
00:34:19,330 --> 00:34:20,930
是在值勤时被杀害的
were killed in the line of duty.

874
00:34:20,965 --> 00:34:22,299
值勤
Duty?

875
00:34:22,333 --> 00:34:23,567
karma公爵
Lord of Karma

876
00:34:23,601 --> 00:34:26,034
是在想阻止一起盗窃行为时被枪击
was shot trying to foil a burglary.

877
00:34:26,069 --> 00:34:28,804
Feverblister是在想要阻止劫车而被刺死
Feverblister was stabbed trying to stop a carjacking.

878
00:34:28,838 --> 00:34:30,105
很不寻常的作案手法
Very different MO's.

879
00:34:30,140 --> 00:34:32,241
但是你提到了一种模式
But you noticed a pattern.

880
00:34:32,276 --> 00:34:34,042
你注意到了我们都注意到的东西
And you noticed that we noticed.

881
00:34:34,077 --> 00:34:37,280
这就是为什么我们有所进展
And that is why we all get along.

882
00:34:37,314 --> 00:34:40,249
现在 每次你带着手机走进一个新的地区
Now, every time you move into a new area with a cell phone,

883
00:34:40,284 --> 00:34:41,983
它都会提醒当地的移动信号塔
it pings the local cell tower.

884
00:34:42,017 --> 00:34:44,286
结果 这个相同的手机出现在
Bottom line, the same cell phone shows up

885
00:34:44,320 --> 00:34:46,120
每一个谋杀现场的附近
in each neighborhood where a murder took place.

886
00:34:46,155 --> 00:34:48,556
这就说明 同一个人
Which means, so does the same person,

887
00:34:48,591 --> 00:34:49,791
出现在几乎相同的时间
at almost the exact same time.

888
00:34:49,825 --> 00:34:51,726
谁
Who?

889
00:34:51,761 --> 00:34:53,961
我们的赢家是
Our winner is...

890
00:34:55,197 --> 00:34:57,665
克莱恩斯・托百特!
Clarence Tobett!

891
00:34:57,699 --> 00:34:59,533
别名ICU
Aka ICU.

892
00:34:59,567 --> 00:35:01,101
看起来托尼是对的
Looks like Tony was right.

893
00:35:01,135 --> 00:35:03,136
头儿 我想他是在比赛中被杀死的
Boss, I think he's been killing the competition.

894
00:35:03,171 --> 00:35:04,805
我不觉得
I don't.

895
00:35:06,641 --> 00:35:09,410
你不能穿着这一身出这个房间
You are not going out of this house in that outfit!

896
00:35:09,444 --> 00:35:10,544
至少不能在大白天
Not in the day!

897
00:35:10,578 --> 00:35:11,712
欧 才怪
Yes, I am.

898
00:35:11,746 --> 00:35:15,281
只要我完成了我的招数
As soon as I finish my Mook Yan Chong kata!

899
00:35:15,316 --> 00:35:16,516
不 实际上 你没有
No, actually, you're not.

900
00:35:16,550 --> 00:35:19,719
噢 天啊 他又犯了什么事儿
Oh, dear Lord, what did he do now?

901
00:35:19,753 --> 00:35:22,288
我们发现了一部属于凶手的手机
We found a cell phone belonging to the murderer.

902
00:35:22,323 --> 00:35:23,856
上面注册是你儿子的名字
It's registered in your son's name.

903
00:35:23,890 --> 00:35:25,925
你们这种行为冒犯了我
I'm offended by insinuation...

904
00:35:25,959 --> 00:35:26,793
住嘴
Shut up!

905
00:35:26,827 --> 00:35:29,028
你再敢说一个字
Don't you say one more word.

906
00:35:29,062 --> 00:35:30,061
把我们的律师叫来
Call our lawyer.

907
00:35:30,095 --> 00:35:31,396
不 我们帮你叫
No, we'll call for you.

908
00:35:31,431 --> 00:35:32,397
姬娃
Ziva.

909
00:35:32,432 --> 00:35:34,700
嗯哼
Mm-hmm.

910
00:35:34,734 --> 00:35:37,035
吉布斯探员 我是把很多人都送进重症监护室
Agent Gibbs, I put plenty of people in the ICU,

911
00:35:37,069 --> 00:35:38,603
但我保证 他们都是罪有应得
but I assure you they all deserved...

912
00:35:38,638 --> 00:35:39,604
闭上你的鸟嘴
Shut up!

913
00:35:39,639 --> 00:35:41,440
你根本就没有送任何人进重症监护室
You didn't put anybody in the ICU.

914
00:35:41,474 --> 00:35:42,541
你只是
All you do is

915
00:35:42,575 --> 00:35:45,343
给医院生病的小孩送了点玩具
give toys to sick kids in hospitals.

916
00:35:45,377 --> 00:35:46,577
你真的是太可悲了
You're pathetic.

917
00:35:49,914 --> 00:35:51,716
哦哦 那是我打的
Oops, that's me.

918
00:35:51,750 --> 00:35:52,883
肯定是拨错了电话号码
Must have dialed the wrong number.

919
00:35:52,917 --> 00:35:54,251
你刚刚拨了什么号码
What number did you dial?

920
00:35:54,285 --> 00:35:55,285
凶手的
The murderer's.

921
00:35:55,320 --> 00:35:56,620
额
Ah.

922
00:35:56,655 --> 00:35:58,389
让我猜猜
Let me guess.

923
00:35:58,423 --> 00:35:59,423
公司电话
Company phone?

924
00:36:00,392 --> 00:36:02,425
你记在你儿子名下的公司
A company you keep in your son's name

925
00:36:02,460 --> 00:36:03,526
作为避税的 对吧
for tax purposes, right?

926
00:36:03,561 --> 00:36:06,028
给我闭嘴 汤姆
Don't you say one thing, Tom.

927
00:36:06,063 --> 00:36:07,464
我们倒是无所谓
That's actually okay with us,

928
00:36:07,498 --> 00:36:09,699
因为你们都有权利保持沉默
because you both have the right to remain silent.

929
00:36:15,439 --> 00:36:17,840
ICU就免了 但是吧
Not quite the ICU, but...

930
00:36:20,777 --> 00:36:23,912
我也想试试
Works for me.

931
00:36:23,946 --> 00:36:25,581
干得好
Nice job.

932
00:36:38,494 --> 00:36:40,695
维恩・托百特是个房产大亨
<i>Wayne Tobett was a slumlord.</i>

933
00:36:40,729 --> 00:36:43,564
他喜欢在犯罪率很高的地段买下便宜的楼盘
His specialty was buying cheap buildings in crime-ridden areas.

934
00:36:43,599 --> 00:36:44,999
犯罪率越高越好
More crime, the better.

935
00:36:45,033 --> 00:36:46,401
房产的价格就会更低
Property values were lowered.

936
00:36:46,435 --> 00:36:48,603
他最不想要的 就是在他看中的地段
The last thing he needed where he was looking to buy

937
00:36:48,637 --> 00:36:50,637
出现社区超级英雄监察团体
was a community watch program on steroids.

938
00:36:50,671 --> 00:36:53,907
但超级英雄偏巧喜欢出没在那
But that's exactly what the Real-Life Superheroes were.

939
00:36:53,941 --> 00:36:56,576
犯罪率下降了 房产价就开始上升了
Crime was down, property values were going up.

940
00:36:56,611 --> 00:36:58,044
他们真的有所作为啊
They were making a difference.

941
00:36:58,078 --> 00:36:59,880
听起来你改变看法了啊
Sounds like you've had a change of heart.

942
00:36:59,914 --> 00:37:02,181
好人就是好人 里昂
Good guys are good guys, Leon.

943
00:37:02,216 --> 00:37:03,583
是啊 坏人很坏
Yeah, bad guys are bad.

944
00:37:03,618 --> 00:37:07,352
他们肯定认识到超级英雄的效应 杀了他们
Figured they'd go in and kill the Superheroes,

945
00:37:07,387 --> 00:37:10,656
犯罪率就会上升 然后他又可以买到廉价物品了
the crime would go up, then they go in and buy cheap.

946
00:37:10,690 --> 00:37:12,324
为什么他们想要炸死那个记者
Why'd they try to blow up the reporter?

947
00:37:12,358 --> 00:37:15,327
温迪揭露了很多有关华盛顿特区房地产的内幕
Wendy had done a fluff piece on real estate in the DC area.

948
00:37:15,361 --> 00:37:17,129
吉布斯探员提到过
Agent Gibbs noticed that

949
00:37:17,163 --> 00:37:19,799
很多廉价房产在那交易
the areas where a lot of cheap buying was going on

950
00:37:19,833 --> 00:37:20,900
同时这地区
were the same areas

951
00:37:20,934 --> 00:37:22,700
正是超级英雄们遇害之地
where Superheroes were being murdered.

952
00:37:22,735 --> 00:37:23,902
避免不了的
Of course he did.

953
00:37:23,936 --> 00:37:25,202
买家就是维恩・托百特
Buyer's Wayne Tobett.

954
00:37:25,237 --> 00:37:26,704
我们猜他越来越紧张了
We think he started getting nervous

955
00:37:26,739 --> 00:37:28,473
因为温迪和我们做出同样的猜测
Wendy would make the same connection we did.

956
00:37:28,507 --> 00:37:30,007
不错
Nice work.

957
00:37:30,042 --> 00:37:31,543
特别是你 吉布斯探员
Especially you, Agent Gibbs.

958
00:37:31,577 --> 00:37:33,210
或者我应该说丘比特
Or should I say Cupid?

959
00:37:33,245 --> 00:37:35,112
毕竟今天是情人节
It is Valentine's Day, after all.

960
00:37:38,616 --> 00:37:41,284
头儿 他在暗示什么?
Boss, what's he talking about?

961
00:37:49,260 --> 00:37:51,127
嗨
Hey.

962
00:37:51,162 --> 00:37:54,063
看看你
Well... look at you.

963
00:37:54,097 --> 00:37:56,131
当我听说旺斯主管让你来犯罪现场采集图片
When I heard Director Vance was letting you take pictures

964
00:37:56,166 --> 00:37:58,634
我不得不亲眼证实一下
of the crime scene, I had to see it to believe it.

965
00:37:58,669 --> 00:38:01,303
当他听说我要把疯狂的海军警官的故事
Well, when he heard I changed my story from crazy naval officer

966
00:38:01,338 --> 00:38:04,206
换成杀死社区英雄的房产大亨时
to evil slumlord that killed a dedicated community activist,

967
00:38:04,240 --> 00:38:05,407
他墙裂支持啊
he got very agreeable.

968
00:38:05,442 --> 00:38:06,375
恩
Mm.

969
00:38:06,409 --> 00:38:08,143
很喜欢你的靴子
Really like those boots.

970
00:38:08,178 --> 00:38:10,278
谢谢啊
Thank you very much.

971
00:38:12,081 --> 00:38:13,949
我们在暗示你退下了 博思寇
That's your cue to leave, Bosco.

972
00:38:13,983 --> 00:38:15,350
谢谢
Thank you, sir.

973
00:38:15,384 --> 00:38:17,586
那个人
That guy.

974
00:38:19,254 --> 00:38:21,322
看起来 看起来
Look... Look...

975
00:38:23,593 --> 00:38:25,526
那么 我 恩 那么
So, I... Hmm. So...

976
00:38:25,560 --> 00:38:28,863
或许我们应该一个一个地说吧
Maybe we should take turns.

977
00:38:28,897 --> 00:38:31,932
女士优先
Ladies first.

978
00:38:31,967 --> 00:38:34,568
我对你说谎了 托尼
I lied to you, Tony.

979
00:38:34,603 --> 00:38:36,403
关于啥
About?

980
00:38:36,437 --> 00:38:38,672
为什么我邀请去早午餐
Why I invited you to brunch.

981
00:38:38,707 --> 00:38:42,542
你错了 我并不是想要得到那个故事的信息
You were wrong; I was not trying to get information for a story.

982
00:38:42,576 --> 00:38:45,845
我要请你是因为我想要见到你
I invited you because I wanted to see you.

983
00:38:48,482 --> 00:38:50,216
该你了
Your turn.

984
00:38:50,250 --> 00:38:51,584
为什吗
Why?

985
00:38:51,619 --> 00:38:54,854
呃 因为我们要轮流着来啊 现在该你说了
Uh, because we're taking turns, and now it's your turn.

986
00:38:54,889 --> 00:38:58,624
不对 这个不是我的本意 而且你知道的
No, that is not what I meant, and you know it.

987
00:38:58,658 --> 00:39:00,859
你想知道我为什么离开
You want to know why I left.

988
00:39:00,894 --> 00:39:03,795
我想知道的是你为啥要对我说 是的
I want to know why you said yes to me

989
00:39:03,830 --> 00:39:05,296
可答案本应该是 不
when the answer was really no.

990
00:39:05,331 --> 00:39:07,766
我很想知道为何你一直等着
I want to know why you waited

991
00:39:07,800 --> 00:39:10,068
直到最后才告诉我真相
until the very last minute to tell me the truth.

992
00:39:10,102 --> 00:39:14,105
但最想知道的是 我的落跑新娘为何要离开
But most of all, my runaway bride, I would like to know why.

993
00:39:14,140 --> 00:39:17,175
好吧 为什么现在不能做出变化呢
Well, would it make a difference now?

994
00:39:17,209 --> 00:39:19,744
我的意思是 如果你不觉得很难受
I mean, if you weren't so sad

995
00:39:19,778 --> 00:39:22,780
很孤单 你根本就不会去思考
and so lonely, you wouldn't even be wondering.

996
00:39:22,814 --> 00:39:24,582
是
Are...

997
00:39:24,616 --> 00:39:25,550
悲伤和孤独
Sad and lonely?

998
00:39:25,584 --> 00:39:28,553
你是不是把我跟博思寇搞混了
You have me confused with Bosco.

999
00:39:28,587 --> 00:39:30,754
你想看看我的女友小文档吗
You like to see my little black e-book?

1000
00:39:30,788 --> 00:39:32,222
无论你给我看什么
Show me whatever you'd like,

1001
00:39:32,257 --> 00:39:35,825
那都不会改变我自己亲眼看到的真相
but it's not gonna change what I see with my own eyes.

1002
00:39:35,860 --> 00:39:39,296
你应该告诉她你的感觉 不论她是谁
You should tell her how you feel, whoever she is.

1003
00:39:43,435 --> 00:39:45,001
A 那根本不会发生
A) That's not gonna happen.

1004
00:39:45,036 --> 00:39:46,569
B 离开我的视界
B) Get out of my head.

1005
00:39:46,603 --> 00:39:49,805
还有C 回答这个问题
And C) answer the question.

1006
00:39:51,508 --> 00:39:56,345
我离开 是因为没准备好去见他 你懂吗
I left because I wasn't ready to meet the one, okay?

1007
00:39:56,380 --> 00:39:57,947
而你就是那个他
And you were the one.

1008
00:39:57,981 --> 00:39:59,715
这根本就说不过去
That doesn't make any sense.

1009
00:39:59,749 --> 00:40:00,783
你确定
Are you sure?

1010
00:40:00,817 --> 00:40:01,884
因为在我看来
'Cause from what I see,

1011
00:40:01,918 --> 00:40:03,885
你花了过去九年半的时间
you've spent the last nine-and-a-half years

1012
00:40:03,919 --> 00:40:04,986
逃避现实的关系
avoiding real relationships.

1013
00:40:05,020 --> 00:40:07,556
我最开始只是伤心
I was just broken first.

1014
00:40:07,590 --> 00:40:11,326
这就是为什么我离开了我的英雄警察 然后跟一个
Which is why I left my hero cop and married a stockbroker

1015
00:40:11,360 --> 00:40:13,295
只关心钱不关心人的股票经纪人结婚了
who cared more about money than people.

1016
00:40:15,164 --> 00:40:18,466
我当初并未做好面对他的准备 托尼
I wasn't ready to meet the one when we met, Tony.

1017
00:40:18,500 --> 00:40:21,302
但我送去邀请是因为...
But I sent you that invitation because...

1018
00:40:21,336 --> 00:40:23,036
我现在准备好了
I am now.


